Just a note to self that when using libraries like sweetalert for example and then I want to convert to sweetalert2, it would have saved a lot of time to wrap it into a &ldquo;service&rdquo; and import that.
For example I made this js file
services/Alerts.js:
import swal from 'sweetalert2';
export default {
send(title, message, error = false) {
swal(
{
type: error ? &quot;error&quot; : &quot;success&quot;,
title: title,
text: message
}
);
}
}
Then import it into the app or into the component that needs it.

